label("$\mathbf{w}$", (B + C)/2, SW);
dot("$A$", A, E);
dot("$B$", B, W);
dot("$C$", C, S);
[/asy]

The area of the parallelogram determined by $\mathbf{v}$ and $\mathbf{w}$ is
\[|(2)(6) - (-3)(1)| = 15,\]so the area of triangle $ABC$ is $\boxed{\frac{15}{2}}.$

